<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-375] Modify backup/restore process using tar</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-375</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The back up and restore process specified in the Lustre manual; sections 14.8.4, 14.8.5, and 17.3; need to be reviewed and, if necessary, modified to specify the &quot;lustre&quot; and &quot;trusted&quot; xattrs be restored explicitly rather than assuming tar will do this automatically. The correct usage of tar for back up is&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;tar --xattrs -cf &amp;lt;backup&amp;gt;.tar &amp;lt;file list&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To extract files, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;tar --xattrs-include=lustre.* -xf &amp;lt;backup&amp;gt;.tar&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
